Durban - The 'knocker gang', a group of men who rob unsuspecting residents as they leave banks after withdrawing large sums of money, has struck again. 
This time, they robbed a man at the Phoenix Plaza on Monday morning.

It is alleged that four men, armed with rifles robbed a business man as he got left a bank and walked towards his vehicle. 
According to sources at the scene, shots were fired as the gang fled the scene but no injuries were reported. 


 






